[
    {
        "text": "I’m Nicole Holofcener.",
        "start": 0.5,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "And I adapted the book\nand directed the movie,",
        "start": 1.89,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "\"The Land of Steady Habits.\"",
        "start": 4.68,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "This is Ben Mendelsohn\nplaying Anders Hill.",
        "start": 7.12,
        "duration": 2.39
    },
    {
        "text": "He’s left his wife and\nmoved into a condo.",
        "start": 9.51,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "And while he was drunk,\nhe told the cab driver",
        "start": 12.21,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "his old address.",
        "start": 14.92,
        "duration": 1.4
    },
    {
        "text": "And when they pulled up, he\ndidn’t realize where he was.",
        "start": 16.32,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "And then he decided\nto go in anyway.",
        "start": 18.69,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "What the hell?",
        "start": 21.45,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "I wanted this scene —",
        "start": 22.41,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "it’s not in the book —",
        "start": 24.09,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "and I wanted to see\nAnders enjoy being a jerk.",
        "start": 25.61,
        "duration": 5.95
    },
    {
        "text": "But he sort of wears his\njerkiness with pride.",
        "start": 31.56,
        "duration": 6.504
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Who the ____ is in my house?",
        "start": 38.064,
        "duration": 1.956
    },
    {
        "text": "Jesus Christ, Anders.\"",
        "start": 40.02,
        "duration": 2.325
    },
    {
        "text": "And he makes a\nfool of himself.",
        "start": 42.345,
        "duration": 2.245
    },
    {
        "text": "And I think that\nit always helps",
        "start": 44.59,
        "duration": 1.984
    },
    {
        "text": "when a character is drunk, if\nthey need to make a fool out",
        "start": 46.574,
        "duration": 2.416
    },
    {
        "text": "of themselves.",
        "start": 48.99,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "And Ben plays a\nterrific drunk.",
        "start": 49.77,
        "duration": 3.525
    },
    {
        "text": "“You can’t just come in here.\"",
        "start": 53.295,
        "duration": 1.262
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m getting some things\nthat are rightfully mine.\"",
        "start": 54.557,
        "duration": 2.143
    },
    {
        "text": "“No, you’re drunk.\"",
        "start": 56.7,
        "duration": 0.855
    },
    {
        "text": "“Some of this stuff,\nI have a right",
        "start": 57.555,
        "duration": 2.585
    },
    {
        "text": "to have it in my house.\"",
        "start": 60.14,
        "duration": 1.295
    },
    {
        "text": "“I left a whole box\nof stuff for you",
        "start": 61.435,
        "duration": 2.015
    },
    {
        "text": "over here by the door.\"",
        "start": 63.45,
        "duration": 1.852
    },
    {
        "text": "“Then what’s all this?\"",
        "start": 65.302,
        "duration": 1.422
    },
    {
        "text": "“I gave you half.\"",
        "start": 66.724,
        "duration": 2.249
    },
    {
        "text": "And I feel he played\na very subtle drunk.",
        "start": 68.973,
        "duration": 3.443
    },
    {
        "text": "“Oh.\"",
        "start": 72.416,
        "duration": 0.809
    },
    {
        "text": "So he breaks into\nthe house and he",
        "start": 73.225,
        "duration": 1.885
    },
    {
        "text": "goes straight into\nthe refrigerator",
        "start": 75.11,
        "duration": 2.23
    },
    {
        "text": "and doesn’t\nrecognize anything.",
        "start": 77.34,
        "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
        "text": "I wanted really like\nairy, fairy healthy crap",
        "start": 78.75,
        "duration": 3.99
    },
    {
        "text": "in the freezer that would\nnot have been in his house.",
        "start": 82.74,
        "duration": 2.915
    },
    {
        "text": "We shoot the refrigerator.",
        "start": 85.655,
        "duration": 2.635
    },
    {
        "text": "I think we had a\nfake light in it.",
        "start": 88.29,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "Because the\nrefrigerator is noisy.",
        "start": 90.66,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "So we turn it off for\nthe sound department.",
        "start": 92.44,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "And by the time we\ngot to the next scene,",
        "start": 94.68,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "where he’s eating a\nPopsicle, the refrigerator",
        "start": 96.39,
        "duration": 5.16
    },
    {
        "text": "had been turned off.",
        "start": 101.55,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "And the Popsicles just\nkept cracking in half",
        "start": 103.26,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "and falling on the floor.",
        "start": 105.72,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "That was pretty sad.",
        "start": 107.1,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": "It was like, what happened?",
        "start": 108.0,
        "duration": 0.93
    },
    {
        "text": "Why don’t they freeze?",
        "start": 108.93,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": "Why don’t they freeze?",
        "start": 109.83,
        "duration": 0.75
    },
    {
        "text": "And then we realized\nthe prop department",
        "start": 110.58,
        "duration": 1.666
    },
    {
        "text": "didn’t realize that they had\nnot turned the power back on.",
        "start": 112.246,
        "duration": 5.074
    }
]